# Suppressions for mobile/package-lock.json findings that cannot be fixed
# without a breaking Expo SDK upgrade (~52.0.0 -> ^57.0.8). npm's own
# dependency graph pins these three packages via @expo/cli/@expo/config-plugins
# to versions below their fixed release; `npm audit fix --force` will bump
# expo/expo-asset/expo-linking to SDK 57 but leaves expo-camera,
# expo-location, expo-local-authentication, expo-modules-core, and
# react-native on their SDK-52-era versions -- a mismatched half-upgrade
# that risks native-module ABI breakage in exactly the two features this
# app depends on most (camera capture, fingerprint auth). A real fix needs
# `npx expo install --fix` plus full device/simulator testing across all
# expo-* packages in lockstep, tracked separately from this CI gate fix.
#
# All three packages below are Expo CLI / Metro build-tooling dependencies
# (plist generation, Metro's CSS pipeline, build-cache tarball extraction)
# that run on the developer/CI machine during `expo start`/`expo build` --
# they are not bundled into the compiled mobile app shipped to end users.
#
# Revisit when the Expo SDK upgrade above is actually done (drop this file
# entirely once expo-camera/expo-location/react-native etc. are aligned to
# a version line where these advisories are fixed upstream).

# @xmldom/xmldom <=0.8.12 -- via @expo/plist (pinned by @expo/config-plugins)
CVE-2026-34601
CVE-2026-41672
CVE-2026-41673
CVE-2026-41674
CVE-2026-41675

# postcss <=8.5.11 -- via @expo/metro-config
